article.headline: Belmont 74, North Florida 54
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Justin Hare scored 17 points to lead Belmont to a 74-54 win over North Florida on Saturday in the regular-season finale for both teams. Belmont (20-9, 14-4) continued its hot shooting from beyond the 3-point line by sinking 12-of-31 attempts from that range. The team raced to a 28-9 lead in the first half and led 35-15 at halftime. Hare missed all five of his 3-point attempts but was perfect on his other five shots from the floor. He also made 7-of-10 free throws. Belmont's 6-foot-10 center Boomer Herndon scored 10 points and blocked eight shots, an Atlantic Sun Conference high this season. James Grimball led North Florida (3-26, 1-17) with 17 points and 11 rebounds.
